<item>
            <title>[SPARK-3121] Wrong implementation of implicit bytesWritableConverter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-3121</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;val path = ... //path to seq file with BytesWritable as type of both key and value&lt;br/&gt;
val file = sc.sequenceFile[Array&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Byte&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;,Array&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Byte&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;](path)&lt;br/&gt;
file.take(1)(0)._1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This prints incorrect content of byte array. Actual content starts with correct one and some &quot;random&quot; bytes and zeros are appended. BytesWritable has two methods:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;getBytes() - return content of all internal array which is often longer then actual value stored. It usually contains the rest of previous longer values&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;copyBytes() - return just begining of internal array determined by internal length property&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like in implicit conversion between BytesWritable and Array&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;byte&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; getBytes is used instead of correct copyBytes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
